> This hearty, speedy kale and mixed greens salad is packed with juicy grape tomatoes, cucumber, and pickled shallot for an impressively colorful bowl. Toss it all together with tangy, Cajun-spiced ranch dressing, then top with juicy slices of sizzled steak for a bold, satisfying spin on a classic (in just 20 minutes!).

== Pickled Shallot ==

Trim, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}. Halve @lemon{1}. Remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%ounce}; chop if desired. Trim and thinly slice @mini cucumber{1}.

In a small #microwave-safe bowl{}, mix shallot, @sugar{1%tsp}, juice from half the lemon, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cover bowl with #plastic wrap{} and microwave ~{1%minute}.

Set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally.

== Cajun Ranch Dressing ==

Place kale in a large #bowl{}; using your hands, massage kale (similar to how you would knead dough) with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} and a pinch of salt until leaves are tender, ~{1%minute}.

In a second small bowl, whisk together @buttermilk ranch dressing{3%ounce}, @sour cream{1.5%ounce}, @cajun spice blend{1%tsp}, and as much @hot sauce{1%tsp} as you like.

== Steak and Salad ==

Wash and dry produce.

Pat @ranch steak{10%ounce} dry and season with salt and pepper. Drizzle @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a hot #medium pan{}. Cook steak to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per side.

> While steak cooks, move on to the next step.

Transfer Cajun ranch dressing to bowl with kale. Add @mixed greens{2%ounce}, cucumber, @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}, and half the pickled shallot (draining first); toss to combine. Season with salt and pepper.

Thinly slice steak against the grain.

Top salad with steak and remaining pickled shallot (draining first). Serve.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.